  "text": "which relates the so-called heat transfer, i.e., the dissipative work, with a quotient of probability densities in the forward and backward trajectories. Now, it becomes clear that the use of the Einstein relation μ D = k B T allows the introduction of the bath temperature to find the entropy production in the environment related to the dissipative work and the quotient of weights associated with the trajectories. It has been shown in the literature that this so-called entropy change satisfies the \"integral fluctuation theorem\"(IFT) [CITATION_1] , < exp −Δηtot >= 1",
